    "Node Sizing Math: 8 application services (api-gateway, api, user, project, task, postgresql, mysql, mongo). Defaulting to 512 Mi per pod = 4096 Mi total. t3.small provides 1.4 GiB allocatable. 4096 Mi / 1433 Mi = ~2.85 nodes. Adding 1 extra node to comfortably accommodate system add-ons (CoreDNS, AWS LBC, EBS CSI), resulting in a desired_node_count of 4.",
    "Kompose Discrepancy: Kompose generated raw Pod objects instead of Deployments/StatefulSets due to 'restart: \"no\"' in the Docker Compose file. The final implementation must convert the stateless services into Deployments and the databases into StatefulSets for high availability and K8s best practices.",
    "Storage & Add-ons: The databases (mysql, postgresql, mongo) require Persistent Volume Claims (PVCs) for their runtime data paths. The AWS EBS CSI driver add-on must be provisioned along with IRSA, and a default StorageClass must be explicitly defined to prevent PVCs from remaining in a Pending state.",
    "Ingress Configuration: 'api-gateway' is the only externally reachable service. AWS Load Balancer Controller will be provisioned to manage an internet-facing Application Load Balancer mapping HTTP traffic to the 'api-gateway' ClusterIP service. No TLS is configured for the baseline; HTTP validation is sufficient.",
    "Core EKS Add-ons: vpc-cni (with before_compute = true), kube-proxy, and coredns are mandatory baseline add-ons required for the cluster's nodes and pods to communicate successfully."
